dflowers, shake the heads to remove dirt and bugs before using.","Citric acid is used to preserve the cordial, and can be purchased from pharmacies or shops stocking Asian ingredients.","Only use a glass bowl or stainless steel pan for the infusing.","Undiluted cordial will keep for several months in the fridge.","The cordial also works well poured over ice cream or drizzled over a plain sponge cake.","Refreshing and fragrant, homemade elderflower cordial is so much better and more pleasing than anything you can buy in the shops. The elderflower season is short, and falls in early summer, but makes a great excuse for long walks spent collecting flowers."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","10h 30m","1 total recipe"]}